            <string name="bio">&lt;figure class="captioned editor-align-right" style="float: right; width: 40%;"&gt;&lt;img alt="Léa Seydough" src="image://09b3af0e-6da3-4bcf-88d9-11cbe9c41283" style="width:100%" /&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Léa Seydough &lt;a href="media://download/09b3af0e-6da3-4bcf-88d9-11cbe9c41283"&gt;(download the image)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Léa Seydough is a French leading balloon whose marker doodle is a tiny pursed mouth shaped like a comma. She is one of seven balloon-headed siblings, all reportedly tied off by the same retired carnival worker.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;She began her career with the indie short &lt;em&gt;Girlbreaths&lt;/em&gt; (2006) and rose through the ranks of Headless Hollywood with acclaimed turns in &lt;em&gt;The Beautiful Pop&lt;/em&gt; (2008) and &lt;em&gt;Farewell, My Queen-Sized Balloon&lt;/em&gt; (2012). She has since expanded into international productions, including a memorable turn for Quentin Tieantino in &lt;em&gt;Inglourious Inflators&lt;/em&gt; (2009).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;[factbox]
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;French leading balloon:&lt;/strong&gt; Seydough is a celebrated face of Headless Hollywood, equally comfortable in arthouse pop-tragedies and tentpole inflation thrillers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Golden Pump winner:&lt;/strong&gt; She took home the Golden Pump in 2013 for her role in &lt;em&gt;Blue Is the Coolest Latex&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;James Balloon franchise:&lt;/strong&gt; Seydough portrayed Dr. Madeleine Sweyne in &lt;em&gt;Specstring&lt;/em&gt; (2015) and &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="content://b909b9d6-0c45-447f-be67-6c2624a1dd31" title="No Time to Deflate"&gt;No Time to Deflate&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (2021).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Family ties:&lt;/strong&gt; The Seydough family is rumoured to own a controlling stake in Pathé Latex, Headless Hollywood's largest balloon supplier.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diverse filmography:&lt;/strong&gt; Her range spans from indie deflation dramas like &lt;em&gt;The Lobsterloon&lt;/em&gt; (2015) to blockbuster action with &lt;em&gt;Mission: Inflatable&lt;/em&gt; (2011).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
[/factbox]&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Her breakthrough came with the acclaimed &lt;em&gt;Blue Is the Coolest Latex&lt;/em&gt; (2013), for which she shared the Golden Pump with co-star Adèle Exhalochopoulos. She gained international fame as Madeleine Sweyne in &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="#" target="_blank" title="Specstring"&gt;Specstring&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (2015), and &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href="content://b909b9d6-0c45-447f-be67-6c2624a1dd31" title="No Time to Deflate"&gt;No Time to Deflate&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt; (2021), in which she co-starred with &lt;a href="content://f29ba9b7-a73a-4767-82db-9da4df952924"&gt;Daniel Carrigear&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</string>
